		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Ward Churchill</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<table class="infobox biography vcard vevent" cellspacing="5" style="width: 22em; text-align: left; font-size: 88%; line-height: 1.5em; width:22em; font-size:95%; text-align:left;">
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="fn summary" style="text-align:center; font-size: 125%; font-weight: bold; text-align:center; font-size:125%;"><b>Ward Churchill</b></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; padding:4pt; line-height:1.25em; text-align:center; font-size:8pt;"><a href="/wiki/File:Ward_Churchill.jpg" class="image" title="Ward Churchill.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Ward_Churchill.jpg/200px-Ward_Churchill.jpg" width="200" height="267" border="0" /></a><br />
<div style="padding-top:2pt;"><span style="">Ward Churchill speaking at the Bay Area Anarchist Book Fair, May 2005.</span></div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding:0.2em 1.0em 0.2em 0.2em; background:transparent; line-height:1.2em; text-align:left; font-size:90%;">Born</th>
<td class="" style="padding:0.2em; line-height:1.3em; vertical-align:middle; font-size:90%;">October 2, 1947 <span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1947-10-02</span>)</span> <span class="noprint">(age&#160;61)</span><br />
<a href="/wiki/Elmwood,_Illinois" title="Elmwood, Illinois">Elmwood, Illinois</a>, United States</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding:0.2em 1.0em 0.2em 0.2em; background:transparent; line-height:1.2em; text-align:left; font-size:90%;">Occupation</th>
<td class="role" style="padding:0.2em; line-height:1.3em; vertical-align:middle; font-size:90%;"><a href="/wiki/Political_activist" title="Political activist" class="mw-redirect">Political activist</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Ward LeRoy Churchill</b> (born October 2, 1947) is an American writer and <a href="/wiki/Political_activism" title="Political activism" class="mw-redirect">political activist</a>. He was a professor of <a href="/wiki/Ethnic_studies" title="Ethnic studies">ethnic studies</a> at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Colorado_at_Boulder" title="University of Colorado at Boulder">University of Colorado at Boulder</a> from 1990 to 2007. The primary focus of his work is on the historical treatment of political dissenters and <a href="/wiki/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States" title="Native Americans in the United States">Native Americans</a> by the United States. His work features controversial and provocative claims, written in a direct, often confrontational style.</p>
<p>In January 2005, Churchill's work attracted publicity, with the widespread circulation of a 2001 essay, <a href="/wiki/On_the_Justice_of_Roosting_Chickens" title="On the Justice of Roosting Chickens" class="mw-redirect"><i>On the Justice of Roosting Chickens</i></a>. In the essay, he claimed that the <a href="/wiki/September_11,_2001_attacks" title="September 11, 2001 attacks" class="mw-redirect">September 11, 2001 attacks</a> were provoked by U.S. policy, and referred to some people working in the <a href="/wiki/World_Trade_Center" title="World Trade Center">World Trade Center</a> as "technocrats" and "<a href="/wiki/Little_Eichmanns" title="Little Eichmanns">little Eichmanns</a>".<sup id="cite_ref-college-journalist-touched-off-firestorm_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-college-journalist-touched-off-firestorm-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> In March 2005 the University of Colorado began investigating allegations that Churchill had engaged in research misconduct; it reported in June 2006 that he had done so.<sup id="cite_ref-misconduct_report_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-misconduct_report-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> Churchill was fired on July 24, 2007,<sup id="cite_ref-cu-regents-fire-ward-churchill_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-cu-regents-fire-ward-churchill-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> leading to a claim from some scholars that he was fired over the ideas he expressed.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4" title=""><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup> Churchill filed a <a href="/wiki/Lawsuit" title="Lawsuit">lawsuit</a> against the University of Colorado for unlawful termination of employment. In April 2009 a <a href="/wiki/Denver" title="Denver">Denver</a> jury found that Churchill was wrongly fired, awarding him $1 in damages.<sup id="cite_ref-wrongly_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-wrongly-5" title=""><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6" title=""><span>[</span>7<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
