<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="press release" id="CITEREF.5Bhttp:.2F.2Fwww.colorado.edu.2Fnews.2F_CU-Boulder_Office_of_News_Services.5D2005"><a href="http://www.colorado.edu/news/" class="external text" title="http://www.colorado.edu/news/" rel="nofollow">CU-Boulder Office of News Services</a> (2005-09-09). <i><a href="http://www.colorado.edu/news/reports/churchill/standingcommittee.html" class="external text" title="http://www.colorado.edu/news/reports/churchill/standingcommittee.html" rel="nofollow">Statement Regarding Decision Of Standing Committee On Research Misconduct</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/News_release" title="News release">Press release</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.colorado.edu/news/reports/churchill/standingcommittee.html" class="external free" title="http://www.colorado.edu/news/reports/churchill/standingcommittee.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.colorado.edu/news/reports/churchill/standingcommittee.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Statement+Regarding+Decision+Of+Standing+Committee+On+Research+Misconduct&amp;rft.aulast=%5Bhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.colorado.edu%2Fnews%2F+CU-Boulder+Office+of+News+Services%5D&amp;rft.au=%5Bhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.colorado.edu%2Fnews%2F+CU-Boulder+Office+of+News+Services%5D&amp;rft.date=2005-09-09&amp;rft.series=%5B%5BNews+release%7CPress+release%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.colorado.edu%2Fnews%2Freports%2Fchurchill%2Fstandingcommittee.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ward_Churchill"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.rockymountainnews.com/drmn/local/article/0,1299,DRMN_15_4339669,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rockymountainnews.com/drmn/local/article/0,1299,DRMN_15_4339669,00.html" rel="nofollow">"Year in quotes"</a>. <i>Rocky Mountain News</i>. 2005-12-25<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.rockymountainnews.com/drmn/local/article/0,1299,DRMN_15_4339669,00.html" class="external free" title="http://www.rockymountainnews.com/drmn/local/article/0,1299,DRMN_15_4339669,00.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.rockymountainnews.com/drmn/local/article/0,1299,DRMN_15_4339669,00.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Year+in+quotes&amp;rft.atitle=Rocky+Mountain+News&amp;rft.date=2005-12-25&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.rockymountainnews.com%2Fdrmn%2Flocal%2Farticle%2F0%2C1299%2CDRMN_15_4339669%2C00.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ward_Churchill"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> Churchill explained his belief to oral historian <a href="/wiki/David_Barsamian" title="David Barsamian">David Barsamian</a>:
<blockquote>
<p>You could say that five hundred years ago was the basis of blood quantum in Ibero-America. But in Anglo-America, while there was some preoccupation with it, it was not formalized until the passage of the General Allotment Act, mid-1880s. At that point they began to define Indian as being someone who was demonstrably and documentably of at least one-quarter by quantum blood indigenous in a given group. You couldn't be an eighth Cheyenne and an eighth Arapaho and be an Indian. You had to be a quarter Cheyenne or a quarter Arapaho or hopefully a quarter and a quarter. The reason for this was quite clear. They were identifying Indians for purposes of allotting them individual parcels of land in the existing reservation base at that point. If they ran out of Indians identifiable as such, then the rest of the land would be declared surplus. So it was clearly in the interests of the government to create a definition of Indianness that would minimize the number of Indians that were available. It was an economic motivation for the application of this genetic criteria to Indianness in the first place. It's become increasingly so ever since." (<cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFDavid_Barsamian_interviews_Ward_Churchill1995">David Barsamian interviews Ward Churchill (December 1995). "<a href="http://www.zmag.org/ZMag/articles/dec95barsamian.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.zmag.org/ZMag/articles/dec95barsamian.htm" rel="nofollow">Historical and Current Perspectives</a>". <i>Z Magazine</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.zmag.org/ZMag/articles/dec95barsamian.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.zmag.org/ZMag/articles/dec95barsamian.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.zmag.org/ZMag/articles/dec95barsamian.htm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Historical+and+Current+Perspectives&amp;rft.jtitle=Z+Magazine&amp;rft.aulast=David+Barsamian+interviews+Ward+Churchill&amp;rft.au=David+Barsamian+interviews+Ward+Churchill&amp;rft.date=December+1995&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zmag.org%2FZMag%2Farticles%2Fdec95barsamian.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ward_Churchill"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>)</p>
</blockquote>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> Churchill's argument about dilution of tribal membership is controversial, however. According to Circe Sturm, for example, the largest of the federally recognized Cherokee tribes—the <a href="/wiki/Cherokee_Nation_of_Oklahoma" title="Cherokee Nation of Oklahoma">Cherokee Nation of Oklahoma</a>—does not impose any blood quantum requirements for membership. It requires only that an applicant prove descent from a person listed on official Cherokee rolls.(<cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSturm2002">Sturm, Circe (2002). <i>Blood Politics: Race, Culture, and Identity in the Cherokee Nation of Oklahoma</i>. Berkeley CA: University of California Press.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Blood+Politics%3A+Race%2C+Culture%2C+and+Identity+in+the+Cherokee+Nation+of+Oklahoma&amp;rft.aulast=Sturm&amp;rft.aufirst=Circe&amp;rft.au=Sturm%2C+Circe&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.place=Berkeley+CA&amp;rft.pub=University+of+California+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ward_Churchill"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>)</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFWard_Churchill2007">Ward Churchill (2007-07-12). <a href="http://wardchurchill.net/files/churchill_response_to_regents_071207.pdf" class="external text" title="http://wardchurchill.net/files/churchill_response_to_regents_071207.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Submission of Professor Ward Churchill to the Board of Regents of the University of Colorado"</a> (PDF)<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://wardchurchill.net/files/churchill_response_to_regents_071207.pdf" class="external free" title="http://wardchurchill.net/files/churchill_response_to_regents_071207.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://wardchurchill.net/files/churchill_response_to_regents_071207.pdf</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Submission+of+Professor+Ward+Churchill+to+the+Board+of+Regents+of+the+University+of+Colorado&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Ward+Churchill&amp;rft.au=Ward+Churchill&amp;rft.date=2007-07-12&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwardchurchill.net%2Ffiles%2Fchurchill_response_to_regents_071207.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ward_Churchill"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
